<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4396836>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 15–22. Pseudodiamesa branickii-type: 15— mandible (arrow indicates branches of seta interna). P. branickii-type: 16—detail of pecten epipharyngis and premandible (arrows indicate seven scales of pecten epipharyngis and 8–9 teeth of the premandible). Pseudodiamesa nivosa-type: 17—head capsule, A—antenna. P. nivosa-type: 18—mandible (arrow indicates branches of seta interna). P. nivosa-type: 19—detail of pecten epipharyngis and premandible (arrows indicate premandible teeth, SI setae and detail of labral lamellae). Pseudodiamesa: 20—young instar head capsule. Pseudodiamesa: 21—detail of mentum. Pseudokiefferiella parva: 22—head capsule." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4396836/files/figure.png" .

